# MessMaster Project Report Supplement

Full system architecture and current feature inventory are documented in [PROJECT_CONTEXT_REPORT.md](/Users/prakharsharma/Downloads/MessMaster/PROJECT_CONTEXT_REPORT.md). This file is the shorter implementation supplement focused on registration structure, compatibility, seed/reset operations, and recent removals.

## Current Mess Registration Structure

### Mess Registration UI
Current mess registration flow collects:
- Mess Info
  - `messName`
  - `phoneNumber`
  - `location`
  - `messCapacity`
- Menu Setup
  - `numberOfMenuItems`
  - `menuItems[]`
- Inventory Setup
  - `inventoryItems[]`
- Cook Setup
  - `cooks[]`
- Admin Contact
  - `adminName`
  - `adminEmail`
  - `adminPassword`
  - `adminPhoneNumber`

### Admin Structure
- Admin / POC / Representative duplication has been collapsed into a single admin source-of-truth for new registrations.
- New backend writes:
  - staff `User` account credentials
  - `Mess.adminContact`

## Mess Model Compatibility

### Current source-of-truth
- `Mess.adminContact`
  - `name`
  - `email`
  - `phone`

### Legacy compatibility
- Old fields remain readable:
  - `pointOfContact`
  - `representative`
- Current backend mirrors new admin data into legacy contact fields where needed so existing consumers do not break immediately.

## Menu Setup Behavior

Current menu setup supports:
- Dynamic menu input generation from `numberOfMenuItems`
- Delete one menu entry
- Delete all menu entries
- Auto-resize of `menuItems[]` when count changes

This behavior is part of the active mess registration UI and should be preserved if the flow is recreated.

## Student Mess Selection Compatibility

- Student registration still requires `messId`.
- Student review flow still requires mess selection.
- Student review history remains mess-linked.
- Review date is generated by the server on submission, not typed by the student.

## Seed / Reset / Migration Operations

### Scripts
- `npm run seed`
- `npm run reset:seed`
- `npm run migrate:admin-contact`

### Operational notes
- Local MongoDB access via `MONGODB_URI` is required.
- `reset:seed` drops the database before reseeding.
- `migrate:admin-contact` backfills `adminContact` from legacy fields without deleting existing records.

